- Allowed: "X is Y, while Z is W" (compound sentence)
- NOT allowed: "X is Y. Z is W." (two separate sentences)

### 4.  Answer Addresses Question
- Answer must DIRECTLY and ACCURATELY respond to the question
- Answer must focus on the core topic of the question
- NO tangential or unrelated information

